[[Category:Glossary]]
[[Category:OntologySync-managed-resource]]

A GRIN (gradient-index) lens is a cylindrical optical element whose refractive index varies radially, causing light to follow curved paths through the lens. In Miniscope applications, a GRIN lens is surgically implanted above a brain region of interest to act as an optical relay, bringing the focal plane from deep brain structures up to the surface where the Miniscope can image it.

== Key Properties ==
* Typical diameters: 0.5 mm, 1.0 mm
* Typical lengths: 4-8 mm depending on target depth
* Can be used as a single element or in a compound (relay + objective) configuration
